ONE STEP CHALLENGE
Technical Implementation Specification
Version 1.0 | November 2024
⚡ Fast-Track Evaluation with Maximum Flexibility
 
1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
The One Step Challenge represents the optimal balance between rapid evaluation and comprehensive risk management. This single-phase evaluation system allows traders to customize their challenge parameters while maintaining firm protection through adaptive rules and dynamic pricing.
Key Features:
•	Single evaluation phase (5-10 days minimum)
•	Fully customizable parameters (5-15% profit target, 2-8% daily loss)
•	Adaptive rules based on configuration
•	Scaling up to 5× after validation
•	60-90% profit split customization
2. SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE
2.1 Component Architecture
 ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │                     One Step Challenge System                  │ ├───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤ │                                                                │ │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐       │ │  │ Configuration│  │  Validation  │  │  Monitoring  │       │ │  │   Engine     │◄─►│   Service    │◄─►│   Service    │       │ │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘       │ │         │                  │                  │                │ │         └──────────────────┼──────────────────┘                │ │                           ▼                                    │ │                  ┌──────────────────┐                         │ │                  │  Rules Engine    │                         │ │                  │  (Adaptive)      │                         │ │                  └──────────────────┘                         │ │                           │                                    │ │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐        │ │  │              Trading Platform (MT4/MT5)           │        │ │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘        │ │                           │                                    │ │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐        │ │  │              PostgreSQL + TimescaleDB             │        │ │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘        │ └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
2.2 Microservices Design
services:   configuration-service:     language: Node.js     responsibilities:       - Parameter validation       - Price calculation       - Configuration storage       - Template management        validation-service:     language: Python     responsibilities:       - Trade validation       - Rule enforcement       - Performance metrics       - Challenge completion        monitoring-service:     language: Go     responsibilities:       - Real-time metrics       - Alert management       - Risk scoring       - Performance tracking        rules-engine:     language: Python     responsibilities:       - Adaptive rule application       - News trading detection       - Consistency calculation       - Strategy validation
3. CONFIGURATION PARAMETERS
3.1 Customizable Parameters
Parameter	Min	Max	Default	Impact
Profit Target	5%	15%	8%	Rules & pricing
Daily Loss	2%	8%	4%	Risk exposure
Max Loss	4%	12%	8%	Total risk
Profit Split	60%	90%	75%	Revenue share
Min Trading Days	3	10	5	Weekend rules
Consistency Rule	30%	50%	40%	Best day limit
3.2 Adaptive Rules Matrix
Rules automatically adapt based on configuration:
const adaptiveRules = {     newsTrading: {         condition: "profitTarget > 8%",         action: "ALLOW",         restriction: "5min buffer before/after"     },     weekendHolding: {         condition: "minDays >= 5",         action: "ALLOW",         restriction: "Max exposure 50%"     },     copyTrading: {         condition: "verification passed",         action: "ALLOW",         restriction: "Master account verified"     },     eaBots: {         condition: "!isHighFrequency",         action: "ALLOW",         restriction: "Max 100 trades/day"     } };
4. DYNAMIC PRICING ALGORITHM
4.1 Complete Pricing Implementation
class OneStepPricingEngine {     constructor() {         this.basePrices = {             5000: 39,             10000: 49,             25000: 99,             50000: 199,             100000: 349,             200000: 599         };                  this.adjustmentFactors = {             profitTarget: {                 easy: { threshold: 8, adjustment: 20 },    // per % below                 hard: { threshold: 10, adjustment: -15 }   // per % above             },             dailyLoss: {                 high: { threshold: 5, adjustment: 60 },    // per % above                 low: { threshold: 4, adjustment: -30 }     // per % below             },             maxLoss: {                 high: { threshold: 10, adjustment: 50 },   // per % above                 low: { threshold: 8, adjustment: -25 }     // per % below             },             minDays: {                 quick: { threshold: 5, adjustment: 15 }    // per day below             },             consistency: {                 low: { threshold: 40, adjustment: 2 }      // per % below             },             split: {                 base: 75,                 adjustment: 4                              // per % above base             }         };     }          calculatePrice(config) {         const basePrice = this.basePrices[config.accountSize];         let difficultyAdjustment = 0;         let splitAdjustment = 0;                  // Profit Target Adjustments         if (config.profitTarget < 8) {             difficultyAdjustment += (8 - config.profitTarget) *                  this.adjustmentFactors.profitTarget.easy.adjustment;         } else if (config.profitTarget > 10) {             difficultyAdjustment += (config.profitTarget - 10) *                  this.adjustmentFactors.profitTarget.hard.adjustment;         }                  // Daily Loss Risk Adjustments         if (config.dailyLoss > 5) {             difficultyAdjustment += (config.dailyLoss - 5) *                  this.adjustmentFactors.dailyLoss.high.adjustment;         } else if (config.dailyLoss < 4) {             difficultyAdjustment += (4 - config.dailyLoss) *                  this.adjustmentFactors.dailyLoss.low.adjustment;         }                  // Max Loss Risk Adjustments         if (config.maxLoss > 10) {             difficultyAdjustment += (config.maxLoss - 10) *                  this.adjustmentFactors.maxLoss.high.adjustment;         } else if (config.maxLoss < 8) {             difficultyAdjustment += (8 - config.maxLoss) *                  this.adjustmentFactors.maxLoss.low.adjustment;         }                  // Min Days Adjustment         if (config.minDays < 5) {             difficultyAdjustment += (5 - config.minDays) *                  this.adjustmentFactors.minDays.quick.adjustment;         }                  // Consistency Rule Adjustment         if (config.consistency < 40) {             difficultyAdjustment += (40 - config.consistency) *                  this.adjustmentFactors.consistency.low.adjustment;         }                  // Profit Split Adjustment         splitAdjustment = (config.profitSplit - 75) *              this.adjustmentFactors.split.adjustment;                  // Calculate final price with floor at 50% of base         const finalPrice = Math.max(             basePrice + difficultyAdjustment + splitAdjustment,             basePrice * 0.5         );                  return {             basePrice,             difficultyAdjustment,             splitAdjustment,             finalPrice: Math.round(finalPrice),             discountEligible: this.checkDiscountEligibility(config)         };     }          checkDiscountEligibility(config) {         // Offer discounts for harder configurations         return config.profitTarget > 12 ||                 config.dailyLoss < 3 ||                 config.consistency > 45;     } }
5. DATABASE SCHEMA
-- One Step Challenge evaluations table CREATE TABLE one_step_evaluations (     id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),     user_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id),     account_number VARCHAR(20) UNIQUE NOT NULL,          -- Configuration Parameters     account_size DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,     profit_target DECIMAL(3, 1) NOT NULL CHECK (profit_target BETWEEN 5 AND 15),     daily_loss_percent DECIMAL(3, 1) NOT NULL CHECK (daily_loss_percent BETWEEN 2 AND 8),     max_loss_percent DECIMAL(3, 1) NOT NULL CHECK (max_loss_percent BETWEEN 4 AND 12),     profit_split INTEGER NOT NULL CHECK (profit_split BETWEEN 60 AND 90),     min_trading_days INTEGER NOT NULL CHECK (min_trading_days BETWEEN 3 AND 10),     consistency_rule DECIMAL(3, 1) NOT NULL CHECK (consistency_rule BETWEEN 30 AND 50),          -- Adaptive Rules (based on configuration)     news_trading_allowed BOOLEAN NOT NULL,     weekend_holding_allowed BOOLEAN NOT NULL,     copy_trading_allowed BOOLEAN NOT NULL,     ea_bots_allowed BOOLEAN NOT NULL,          -- Pricing     base_price DECIMAL(8, 2) NOT NULL,     difficulty_adjustment DECIMAL(8, 2) NOT NULL,     split_adjustment DECIMAL(8, 2) NOT NULL,     final_price DECIMAL(8, 2) NOT NULL,     discount_applied DECIMAL(5, 2) DEFAULT 0,          -- Status & Timeline     status VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'active',     created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),     started_at TIMESTAMP,     passed_at TIMESTAMP,     failed_at TIMESTAMP,     funded_at TIMESTAMP,          -- Performance Metrics     current_balance DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,     starting_balance DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,     peak_balance DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,     lowest_balance DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,     profit_target_amount DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,     daily_loss_limit DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,     max_loss_limit DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,          -- Trading Statistics     total_trades INTEGER DEFAULT 0,     winning_trades INTEGER DEFAULT 0,     losing_trades INTEGER DEFAULT 0,     trading_days INTEGER DEFAULT 0,     best_day_profit DECIMAL(10, 2) DEFAULT 0,     worst_day_loss DECIMAL(10, 2) DEFAULT 0,     consistency_score DECIMAL(5, 2),          -- Risk Metrics     risk_score DECIMAL(4, 2),     sharpe_ratio DECIMAL(4, 2),     max_drawdown DECIMAL(5, 2),     win_rate DECIMAL(5, 2),     average_rr DECIMAL(4, 2), -- Risk:Reward ratio          -- Validation Flags     has_minimum_trades BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,     meets_consistency BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,     meets_profit_target BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,     no_rule_violations BOOLEAN DEFAULT TRUE,          INDEX idx_user_id (user_id),     INDEX idx_status (status),     INDEX idx_created_at (created_at),     INDEX idx_risk_score (risk_score) );
-- Challenge progress tracking CREATE TABLE one_step_progress (     id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),     evaluation_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES one_step_evaluations(id),     date DATE NOT NULL,          -- Daily Metrics     starting_balance DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,     ending_balance DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,     daily_pnl DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,     daily_pnl_percent DECIMAL(5, 2) NOT NULL,          -- Trading Activity     trades_count INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,     volume_traded DECIMAL(12, 2),     commission_paid DECIMAL(8, 2),          -- Risk Metrics     daily_drawdown DECIMAL(10, 2),     daily_drawdown_percent DECIMAL(5, 2),     max_position_size DECIMAL(10, 2),          -- Validation     is_trading_day BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE,     has_news_trades BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,     has_weekend_holds BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,          UNIQUE(evaluation_id, date),     INDEX idx_evaluation_date (evaluation_id, date) );
